{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> τοιόσδε</b>, άδε <br /> (<i>Ionic dialect</i> ήδε), όνδε, a form of τοῖος, bearing the same relation to τοιοῦτος as ὅδε to οὗτος, <b>such as this,</b> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus not so common as τοῖος, but in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] and <i>Attic dialect</i> much more so; sometimes <i>antecedent</i> to οἷος, as ἀοιδοῦ τοιοῦδ᾽ οἷος ὅδ᾽ ἐστί [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.371, compare 17.313, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.375: but more frequently _absolutely_, ἀλλ᾽ ὅδ᾽ ἐγὼ τ.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] here am I <b>such as you see,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.205, compare 15.330 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; frequently with implications, <b>so great, so bad,</b> etc.; οὔ κε κακοὶ τοιούσδε τέκοιεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.64; τοιόσδε τοσόσδε τε λαός 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.120, 799 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τοιάδε λαίφεα <b>such</b> clothes, i. e. <b>so bad,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.206; τοσόσδε καὶ τοιόσδε 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.73: after 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus antecedent to οἷος, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 576.2, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Meno” 75e, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; to ὅς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.158 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; rarely to a <i>conjunction</i>, as ὡς, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 179 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with a qualifying word, τοιόσδ᾽ ἠμὲν δέμας ἠδὲ καὶ ἔργα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 17.313; τοιόσδ᾽ ἐστὶ πόδας 19.359: with the _Article_, ὁ τ. ἀνήρ, αἱ τ. πράξεις, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 547, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 895 (Lyric poetry); ἐν τῇ τ. ἀνάγκῃ 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.10; οἱ τοιοίδε 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 330; τὸ τ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 358b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν τῷ τοιῷδε in <b>such</b> circumstances, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.27, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.36, etc.: without _Article_, κατὰ τοιόνδε\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] in <b>such</b> wise, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.48, 7.10. ; ἕτεροι τ. [prev. author] 1.207; φωνῆς ἐνεχθείσης τοιᾶσδε NT.2Pet.1.17: the sense is made more _indefinite_ by τοιόσδε τις,\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>] <b>such a</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.139, 4.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], frequently in <i>Attic dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 173e, +others: in prose narrative τοιάδε\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] is, properly, <b>as follows,</b> τοιαῦτα <b>as aforesaid,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.8, +others (compare ὅδε, οὗτος)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but this distinction is not strictly observed. <i>adverb</i> τοιῶσδε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Adamantius Physiognomonicus “Vent.” 37, 39, 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis ad 2nd c.AD: Dionysius Periegeta “Prooem.” p.82 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus, etc. [τοῐ- in 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 239, “Ag.” 1400, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 435, “Aj.” 453 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but not so frequently as in τοιοῦτος.]","strongNumber":"G5107","accentedUnicode":"τοιόσδε","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1161","matchingForm":"δέ","stepTransliteration":"de","gloss":"then","_zh_tw_Gloss":"但, 並且","_es_Gloss":"pero/y ","_zh_Gloss":"但, 并且"},{"strongNumber":"G5104","matchingForm":"τοί","stepTransliteration":"toi","gloss":"certainly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"只是","_es_Gloss":"ciertamente","_zh_Gloss":"只是"}],"shortDef":"such as this, of this kind","mediumDef":"such as this, of this kind <br /><b>such as this; such as follows, of this kind</b> <ref='2Pe.1.17'>2Pet. 1:17</ref>*","stepGloss":"such as this","stepTransliteration":"toiosde","count":1,"_es_Definition":"de tal calidad, de tal tipo","_zh_tw_Definition":"如此 (彼前1:7)","_zh_Definition":"如此 (彼前1:7)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"như thế, như vậy, thế đó","_zh_tw_Gloss":"有這樣","_es_Gloss":"así como este","_zh_Gloss":"有这样"}]}